Liz Hurley's new TV show has been drubbed by US critics. 

The Royals, starring Hurley as a fictional Queen, and Joan Collins as her feisty mother, was described as ‘not a royally good time’ by The Hollywood Reporter.

The show, which airs tonight in the US, was branded ‘loud and bombastic’, with one critic saying it ‘plays like an extended MTV music video’.

