Meanwhile, Newsday called it ‘trash TV’ and ‘the equivalent of The Real Housewives of Buckingham Palace’.

A source at E! TV, which will broadcast the show in the UK later this month, said: ‘Everyone is very disappointed with the reviews. 

'We were hoping, with such a stellar cast, this would be something that would really appeal.’

 

